Parliament, Tuesday, 03 July 2018 – A delegation of the Joint Constitutional Review Committee will tomorrow hold the last of the Mpumalanga public hearings into the possible review of section 25 of the Constitution in Middelburg. The decision to hold public hearings follows a mandate by the National Assembly and the National Council of Provinces to ascertain whether a review of Section 25 of the Constitution and other clauses are necessary, to make it possible for the state to expropriate land in the public interest without compensation, and propose the necessary constitutional amendments where necessary. Details of the Hearings Date: Wednesday, 04 July 2018
	Venue: Adelaide Tambo Hall (Middelburg)
	Time: 11:00-16:00 ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CO-CHAIRPERSON OF THE JOINT CONSTITUTIONAL REVIEW COMMITTEE, MR VINCENT SMITH For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Malatswa Molepo (Mr)
